title: Grateful Dead Live at Starlight Theater on 1982-08-03
lineage: TDK-MA > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain SRC > Wavelab (adding 16-bit patches) > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F.
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower-> Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, El Paso, Cumberland Blues, Althea-> Cassidy-> Big Railroad Blues, Women Are Smarter, Might As Well

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, To Lay Me Down-> Let It Grow-> Drums-> He's Gone-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: great recording of an epic 82 show take a listen to the very staccato space and the beautiful He's Gone that arises out of it...

Great sound  This is a great sounding recording, hope you have a copy of aud from the 8 4 82 show. Have never heard one please if you have one in your collection post it. please please please.
 Back to this night at Starlight . was an amazing night of music in the days when there not thousands on tour. This show shines . Is one of my favorite nights during a summer of gems

good recording, mediocre show, sweet Stella Jerry has a bit of a sore throat, so his vocals are rough. Band is tired sounding, not much magic. Both Bob and Jerry flub lyrics and generally sound a bit shaky/buzzed/sloppy.

The Stella Blue, however, shines! 

It is really a gem, and Jerry uses his voice here perfectly, flaws and all...amazing how he pulls it together for this one. 

To be honest, one of the most amazing things about Jerry and the Dead was how they could  amaze us with a tender ballad like this sometimes...with Jerry exposing a fragility and emotion and soul so deep....it is special.
